<td rowspan="2"><sup id="cite_ref-22" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-22">&#91;22&#93;</a></sup>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="/wiki/Academy_Award_for_Best_Director" title="Academy Award for Best Director">Best Director</a></td>
<td style="background: #FFE3E3; color: black; vertical-align: middle; text-align: center;" class="no table-no2 notheme">Nominated</td>
<td><a href="/wiki/William_Wyler" title="William Wyler">William Wyler</a> – <i><a href="/wiki/Ben-Hur_(1959_film)" title="Ben-Hur (1959 film)">Ben-Hur</a></i>
</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<p>As a <a href="/wiki/Lieutenant_colonel" title="Lieutenant colonel">lieutenant colonel</a> in the U.S. Army, Stevens headed the Signal Corps unit that filmed D-Day and the liberation of the Dachau concentration camp. For these contributions, he was awarded the <a href="/wiki/Legion_of_Merit" title="Legion of Merit">Legion of Merit</a>.
</p><p>Stevens has a star on the <a href="/wiki/Hollywood_Walk_of_Fame" title="Hollywood Walk of Fame">Hollywood Walk of Fame</a> at 1701 Vine Street. He won the <a href="/wiki/Academy_Award_for_Best_Director" title="Academy Award for Best Director">Academy Award for Best Director</a> twice, in 1951 for <i>A Place in the Sun</i> and in 1956 for <i>Giant</i>. He was also nominated in 1943 for <i><a href="/wiki/The_More_the_Merrier" title="The More the Merrier">The More the Merrier</a></i>, in 1954 for <i>Shane</i>, and in 1959 for <i>The Diary of Anne Frank</i>.
</p><p>He also received both the <a href="/wiki/Irving_G._Thalberg_Memorial_Award" title="Irving G. Thalberg Memorial Award">Irving G. Thalberg Memorial Award</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Academy_Honorary_Award" title="Academy Honorary Award">Lifetime Achievement Award</a> from the <a href="/wiki/Academy_of_Motion_Picture_Arts_and_Sciences" title="Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences">Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences</a> (1954). He also received the <a href="/wiki/National_Board_of_Review_Award_for_Best_Director" title="National Board of Review Award for Best Director">National Board of Review Award for Best Director</a> and the <a href="/wiki/New_York_Film_Critics_Circle_Award_for_Best_Director" title="New York Film Critics Circle Award for Best Director">New York Film Critics Circle Award for Best Director</a>.
</p>
